In this thread, I will discuss the colonial invention of the religion called &ldquo;Buddhism&rdquo;. I will summarize some arguments from S.N. Balagangadhara&rsquo;s book &ldquo;Do all roads lead to Jerusalem?&rdquo;
I will quote some old colonial literature in parallel. Most people don&rsquo;t know that the understanding that Buddhism is a different religion from the paganism of Asia (also called as &ldquo;Hindooism&rdquo;) was a very late one. The early colonial literature doesn&rsquo;t mention it.
